summary:
The Security Council, determining the situation in the Former Yugoslavia remains a threat to international peace and security, 

Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United Nations, 

1. Authorizes a multinational stabilization force (EUFOR ALTHEA) for 12 months to fulfil its missions in relation to the implementation of Annex 1-A and Annex 2 of the General Framework Agreement for Peace in Bosnia and Herzegovina;

2. Renews the authorization provided by paragraph 11 of its resolution 2183 (2014) for 12 months;

3. Authorizes Member States to take measures to ensure compliance with Annexes 1-A and 2, and stresses parties' equal responsibility for compliance;

4. Authorizes Member States to take measures in defence of EUFOR ALTHEA or NATO presence and to assist them in carrying out their missions;

5. Authorizes Member States to ensure compliance with airspace rules and procedures over Bosnia and Herzegovina;

6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
